File: Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize. JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize has welcomed Nehawu's fact finding report on PPE and health worker shortages. The union's report revealed the dire state of public health care and risky working conditions at some hospitals. READ: COVID-19: Nehawu calls on members to down tools It's asked frontline workers to stay at home on 28 August to highlight their demands. Mkhize has applauded the reporting of non-compliance and says his department needs to urgently respond to shortfalls. READ: Nehawu concerned about health workers contracting COVID-19 He also thanked the men and women in the health sector for their efforts in curbing the spread of COVID-19.